705388f-b.text:
125 Lake Place, at the N.E. corner of West 6th Street, showing one of the many old one family homes that are fast disappearing in Brooklyn. This set of three views were taken at the same time and exclusive of No. 3 (which shows West 6th Street) are identical.
April 25, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
